article.description: Freshman Jasmine Lister scored 17 points, including hitting a career-high five 3-pointers, and Stephanie Holzer added 16 points to help Vanderbilt upset Arkansas 65-54 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Jasmine Lister leads Vanderbilt to upset of No. 24 Arkansas
article.linkText: Vandy upsets Arkansas to stay perfect at home
article.story:
NASHVILLE, Tenn. --  Freshman Jasmine Lister scored 17 points, including hitting a career-high five 3-pointers, and Stephanie Holzer added 16 points to help Vanderbilt upset Arkansas (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) 65-54 on Thursday night.

Lister hit her first five shots, including all four 3s, for the Commodores (13-6, 4-2 Southeastern Conference), who entered the game tied with the Razorbacks (15-3, 3-3) for fourth place in the conference.

C'eira Ricketts scored a career-high 29 points, including 11 of the team's final 14 to lead Arkansas. Ashley Daniels added 10 points for the Razorbacks.

With the game tied at 30, Vanderbilt scored the next nine points. After Arkansas came within 39-35 the Commodores used a 17-5 run to put the game away.

Christina Foggie hit two 3-pointers during the spurt as Vanderbilt led 56-40 with 7:49 left.

She finished with 10 points and Jence Rhoads had 13 for Vanderbilt, which is 10-0 at home this season.
